data.title: Private equity deal value reached a record US$310b, with exit activity rising 40%. Fundraising stayed soft but could improve with new retail channels.
data.description: Progress in deals was accelerated due to decreasing valuation disparities and better funding circumstances, resulting in the highest deployment numbers on record. Exit operations saw a significant 40% increase compared to the previous year, primarily due to the robust performance of IPO markets. While fundraising activity was relatively subdued, the introduction of new retail avenues and expanded access to the US 401(k) system hint at future potential for growth in this area.

data.title: Novo Nordisk offers $9 billion counteroffer for Metsera, challenging Pfizer's $4.9 billion acquisition.
data.description: Metsera Inc. (NASDAQ: MTSR) recently received an unexpected acquisition offer from Novo Nordisk A/S (NYSE: NVO), with the proposal deemed a "Superior Company Proposal" compared to Metsera's current Merger Agreement with Pfizer Inc (NYSE: PFE), who had previously agreed to purchase Metsera for $47.50 per share in cash, totaling around $4.9 billion. This deal would provide Pfizer with a set of unique oral and injectable incretin, non-incretin, and combination therapy candidates. Novo Nordisk's proposal is outlined in two phases, with the initial phase involving a payment of $56.50 per share in cash to Metsera upon the finalization of a definitive agreement, along with additional amounts pertaining to Metsera employee equity and transaction costs. For further details, visit a reliable financial news platform.

data.title: Delta Black Aerospace and Taqtile team up to modernize military drone maintenance with Manifest platform.
data.description: In McKinney, Texas, Delta Black Aerospace, a defense manufacturer in the U.S., specializing in advanced unmanned aerial systems for critical missions, has partnered with Taqtile, the developer of the Manifest® digital work instruction platform. This strategic collaboration aims to revolutionize maintenance operations for military systems and enhance the upkeep of technologically advanced equipment at the frontline. Delta Black will incorporate Taqtile’s Manifest platform throughout its operations, introducing modernization to sustainment processes.

data.title: Inventor from Houston develops Tumbler Frying Machine to rotate food items for even frying.
data.description: In Pittsburgh on October 30, 2025, an inventor from Houston, Texas shared his creation, the TUMBLER FRYING MACHINE/ ROTATING FRYER. The innovative machine automatically rotates food items as they fry to ensure even frying. This inventive solution aims to improve the quality of fried foods by ensuring consistent cooking. The inventor highlighted the importance of this design feature in achieving evenly fried food items.
